<h3>GRID</h3>

<p><b>Siimple</b> uses a responsive <code>grid</code> with 12 columns, and a max width of <b>960px</b>.
If you want a full width grid, add the <code>grid-fluid</code> class to the main grid container.
Add a <code>col-#</code> class to every column, where # is a number from 1 to 12. For example: </p>

<!-- Grid demo -->
<div class="grid grid-fluid">
  <div class="row docs-row">
    <div class="col-12 docs-col">Col 12</div>
  </div>
  <div class="row docs-row">
    <div class="col-1 docs-col">Col 1</div>
    <div class="col-11 docs-col">Col 11</div>
  </div>
  <div class="row docs-row">
    <div class="col-2 docs-col">Col 2</div>
    <div class="col-10 docs-col">Col 10</div>
  </div>
  <div class="row docs-row">
    <div class="col-3 docs-col">Col 3</div>
    <div class="col-9 docs-col">Col 9</div>
  </div>
  <div class="row docs-row">
    <div class="col-4 docs-col">Col 4</div>
    <div class="col-8 docs-col">Col 8</div>
  </div>
  <div class="row docs-row">
    <div class="col-5 docs-col">Col 5</div>
    <div class="col-7 docs-col">Col 7</div>
  </div>
  <div class="row docs-row">
    <div class="col-6 docs-col">Col 6</div>
    <div class="col-6 docs-col">Col 6</div>
  </div>
</div>

